üåå Core Concepts

Johnson Reduction Theory

The theory follows the rules:

- 0 = 1
- 19 = 10 when aleph-null equals ashtei-asar-null
- 10 = 1
- 1 = 1
When infinite-compression mode is disabled, numbers remain untouched.

Two reduction paths exist:

1. Johnson Mode (non-numerological, infinity-dependent)
2. Numerology Mode (classic digit reduction, respecting master numbers)

The system allows toggling between:

- Closed Infinity Mode (aleph-null ‚â† ashtei-asar-null)
- Open Infinity Mode (aleph-null = ashtei-asar-null)

Each mode affects how numbers reduce.

